---
block_id: 025
name: hub-bgp-base
display_name: "Hub BGP Base Configuration"
version: 1.0.0
category: core
device_role: hub
vendor: fortinet
platform: fortigate
min_fortios: "7.4.0"

description: |
  BGP base configuration for SD-WAN hub. Establishes AS number, router-ID,
  and BGP timers. Hub uses neighbor-range (added in block 026) to accept
  dynamic spoke BGP sessions.

  KEY: Hub AS is constant (65000), spokes use 65000 + site_id.

depends_on:
  - block_id: 023
    reason: "IPsec phase1 templates must exist for overlay routing"

provides:
  - hub-bgp-base
  - bgp-as-65000
  - hub-routing

parameters:
  - name: BGP_AS
    description: "Hub BGP AS number"
    type: integer
    required: false
    default: 65000
    note: "Hub AS is always 65000"

  - name: ROUTER_ID
    description: "BGP router-ID (typically hub loopback IP)"
    type: ip_address
    required: true
    example: "172.16.255.252"

  - name: IBGP_MULTIPATH
    description: "Enable iBGP multipath"
    type: string
    required: false
    default: "enable"
    allowed_values: ["enable", "disable"]

  - name: GRACEFUL_RESTART
    description: "Enable graceful restart"
    type: string
    required: false
    default: "enable"
    allowed_values: ["enable", "disable"]

  - name: HOLDTIME_TIMER
    description: "BGP hold time in seconds"
    type: integer
    required: false
    default: 180

  - name: KEEPALIVE_TIMER
    description: "BGP keepalive time in seconds"
    type: integer
    required: false
    default: 60

verification:
  commands:
    - "get router bgp"
  expected_patterns:
    - "as: {{BGP_AS}}"
    - "router-id: {{ROUTER_ID}}"
    - "ibgp-multipath: {{IBGP_MULTIPATH}}"

rollback:
  commands:
    - "config router bgp"
    - "unset as"
    - "end"

notes: |
  - Hub AS is 65000 (constant)
  - Spokes use AS 65000 + site_id (e.g., site 7 = AS 65007)
  - iBGP multipath allows ECMP across multiple spoke tunnels
  - Graceful restart prevents route flapping during restarts
  - This block does NOT configure neighbor-range (see block 026)
  - This block does NOT advertise networks (add in separate block if needed)

---

config router bgp
    set as {{BGP_AS}}
    set router-id {{ROUTER_ID}}
    set ibgp-multipath {{IBGP_MULTIPATH}}
    set ebgp-multipath enable
    set additional-path enable
    set additional-path-select 4
    set recursive-next-hop enable
    set recursive-inherit-priority enable
    set graceful-restart {{GRACEFUL_RESTART}}
    set graceful-restart-time 120
    set graceful-stalepath-time 360
    set holdtime-timer {{HOLDTIME_TIMER}}
    set keepalive-timer {{KEEPALIVE_TIMER}}
end
